---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy - The National Angle"
  description="How The National Angle handles visitor data and protects reader privacy."
>
  <article class="infoPage">
    <header class="infoHero">
      <div class="signalPills"><span>Privacy</span><span>Minimal data</span><span>No ad tracking</span></div>
      <h1>Reader Privacy Without Unnecessary Tracking</h1>
      <p class="pageDeck">The National Angle is designed to work without reader accounts, advertising profiles, or intrusive tracking. This page explains the limited technical information that may still be processed when you visit.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="infoGrid">
      <section><p class="cardLabel">01</p><h2>Information You Provide</h2><p>The site currently does not require an account or ask readers to submit personal information. If contact, newsletter, membership, or comment features are introduced, this policy will explain what information those services request before they are used.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">02</p><h2>Technical Delivery Data</h2><p>Our hosting and security providers may process standard connection data such as IP address, browser type, requested page, and request timing. This information may be needed to deliver the site, prevent abuse, and maintain reliability.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">03</p><h2>Cookies and Audience Measurement</h2><p>We do not intentionally use advertising trackers or build advertising profiles. If analytics or other measurement tools are added, this page will identify them and any consent choices required by applicable law.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">04</p><h2>Links and Policy Updates</h2><p>Articles may link to services with their own privacy practices. We may update this policy as the publication develops, and the date below will show when the latest version took effect.</p></section>
    </div>

    <p class="policyDate">Last updated: June 14, 2026</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
